name: Relinquishment no bar to jurisdiction
text: §436B-22  Relinquishment no bar to jurisdiction.  The forfeiture, nonrenewal, surrender, or voluntary relinquishment of a license by a licensee shall not bar jurisdiction by the licensing authority to proceed with any investigation, action, or proceeding to revoke, suspend, condition, or limit the licensee's license or fine the licensee. [L 1991, c 111, pt of §2; am L 1992, c 202, §18]
